How to install python_matchit.vim? https://catonmat.net/vim-plugins-matchit-vim
(Matchit.vim has been included in vim since version 6.0.
Currently using version 8...)

Python_matchit.vim is a filetype plugin. It has to be installed in "ftplugin" directory. Follow these steps to get it installed:

    1. Download python_matchit.vim.
    (http://www.vim.org/scripts/script.php?script_id=386)
    2. Put it in ~/.vim/ftplugin (on Unix/Linux).
    3. Restart Vim or source matchit.vim with ":so ~/.vim/ftplugin/python_matchit.vim".






To enable auto-complete every time a HTML file is opened, add the following line to your ~/.vimrc;

autocmd FileType html set omnifunc=htmlcomplete#CompleteTags



